     <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.brellserilis.net/images/gabby.gif width=101 height=80></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Board Policy: Custom Signatures Rules</span><hr size=1> We are again enabling custom signatures on the board forums. However, we are serious about keeping the size of these signatures down to a reasonable size. For that reason, we have provided these simple guidelines for your custom signatures. We ask that you follow these rules, and we will not need to remove tha ability to post sigs again. We will manually remove offending sigs which break the rules for a time and follow up with a warning. <br>
<br>
1. Java Applets are prohibited<br>
2. Pics will have a height limit of 175pixels.<br>
3. Any pic(especially the personal icons) that distort the forums are prohibited.<br>
4. Pics will have a size limit of 40k<br>
5. Only post your sig pic once per thread. If you plan on replying to a thread in which you have already posted, please click off the option to include your sig pic in your reply. You may have a great sig, but we dont need to see it 10x a thread <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
6. Keep your personal photo as close to 60x60 as possible. Sometimes they need to be larger to remain clear, but please do not have several hundred pixel high personal photos.<br>
<br>
If you have a sig rather large in size it may be because you have taken a larger image and resized it using HTML, I suggest you create it the size that you want it to be.<br>
<br>
If your sig has a ton of text under it, we may ask you to remove some of it as well.<br>
<br>
